<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="50" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/40</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMT1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31T20:00:00+00:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9:50 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>German Ambassador informs me that he has just received instructions from
                            his Government to ask French Government whether they will maintain
                            neutrality in Europe and requests answer by one o’clock to-night. He
                            anticipates immediate reply in the negative. He believes that German
                            Ambassador at Washington has asked the United States to take charge of
                            German Embassy and consulates in France in event of negative reply.
                            German Ambassador here would expect to have American flag raised over
                            German Embassy.</p>
                        <p>Most important to have immediate instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HMT1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>